    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Electronic Signature Standards Act of 2016 </b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to require the Internal Revenue Service to publish guidance to establish uniform standards and procedures for the acceptance of signatures in digital or other electronic form for the purposes of: (1) disclosures of tax returns and return information to a designee of the taxpayer, and (2) any power of attorney executed by the taxpayer. </p>]]></text>
